TY  - JOUR
AU  - Vayanos, Dimitri
T1  - Strategic Trading and Welfare in a Dynamic Market
PY  - 1999
Y1  - 1999/04/01
DO  - 10.1111/1467-937X.00086
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 66
IS  - 2
SP  - 219
EP  - 254
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper studies a dynamic model of a financial market with N strategic agents. Agents receive random stock endowments at each period and trade to share dividend risk. Endowments are the only private information in the model. We find that agents trade slowly even when the time between trades goes to 0. In fact, welfare loss due to strategic behaviour increases as the time between trades decreases. In the limit when the time between trades goes to 0, welfare loss is of order 1/N, and not 1/N2 as in the static models of the double auctions literature. The model is very tractable and closed-form solutions are obtained in a special case.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1467-937X.00086
ER  - 



